==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dicarbonic
<hw>di`car*bon"ic</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧`k⟦aum⟧r*b⟦ocr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>di-</ets> + <ets>carbonic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Containing two carbon residues, or two carboxyl
groups or radicals; <as>as, oxalic acid is the simplest
<ex>dicarbonic</ex> acid</as>. In the latter sense, synonymous with
<altname>dicarboxylic</altname>; <as>as, succinic acid is a
<altname>dicarboxylic</altname> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

